{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"I was born and raised in Dakar, Senegal,"},{"time":3920,"text":"and through a combination\nof accidents and cosmic justice,"},{"time":8960,"text":"became a chef in the US."}]},{"cues":[{"time":10880,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":12680,"text":"When I first arrived in New York,"},{"time":15120,"text":"I began working in these restaurants --\ndifferent types of restaurants --"},{"time":18600,"text":"from French bistro to Italian,"},{"time":21320,"text":"global ethnic to modern American."},{"time":24280,"text":"At the time,"},{"time":25560,"text":"New York was already well-established\nas a food capital of the world."},{"time":30080,"text":"However ..."},{"time":32800,"text":"with the exception of a few West African\nand Ethiopian mom-and-pop eateries,"},{"time":38560,"text":"there was no such thing\nas African cuisine in the entire city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43760,"text":"Early in my life,"},{"time":45280,"text":"I was influenced\nby Senegal's first president,"},{"time":48280,"text":"Léopold Sédar Senghor,"},{"time":51000,"text":"nicknamed, \"the poet president,\""},{"time":53240,"text":"who talked about a new humanism,"},{"time":55600,"text":"a universal civilization,"},{"time":57000,"text":"in which all cultures would come together\naround a communal table as equals,"},{"time":63040,"text":"each bringing its own beautiful\ncontribution to share."},{"time":67680,"text":"He called it \"the rendezvous\nof giving and receiving.\""},{"time":72200,"text":"That concept resonated with me,"},{"time":74520,"text":"and it has guided my career path."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77480,"text":"After years of working in restaurants,"},{"time":80600,"text":"I yearned for my work\nto have a deeper impact"},{"time":83760,"text":"that would go beyond\nthe last meal I had served."},{"time":88600,"text":"I wanted to give back, both to New York --"},{"time":91560,"text":"the city that allowed me\nthe opportunity to follow my calling --"},{"time":95640,"text":"but also to my origins\nand ancestors in Senegal."},{"time":100640,"text":"I wanted to contribute\nto that universal civilization"},{"time":103600,"text":"Senghor had described."},{"time":105880,"text":"But I didn't know how to make\na measurable impact"},{"time":108480,"text":"as a cook and writer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111680,"text":"While I was writing my first cookbook,"},{"time":115000,"text":"I often traveled to different regions\nof Senegal for research."},{"time":120560,"text":"During one of those trips,"},{"time":122720,"text":"in the remote, southeast\nregion of Kédougou"},{"time":126440,"text":"I rediscovered\nan ancient grain called fonio"},{"time":130680,"text":"that had all but disappeared\nfrom the urban Senegalese diet."},{"time":136680,"text":"It turns out that fonio\nhad been cultivated"},{"time":139560,"text":"for more than five thousand years"},{"time":142160,"text":"and is probably the oldest\ncultivated cereal in Africa."},{"time":146760,"text":"Once a popular grain\non much of the continent,"},{"time":151000,"text":"fonio was grown\nall the way to ancient Egypt,"},{"time":154680,"text":"where archaeologists found grains\ninside pyramids' burial grounds."},{"time":160880,"text":"Today it is mostly cultivated\nin the western part of the Sahel region,"},{"time":166640,"text":"from Senegal to Mali,"},{"time":168960,"text":"Burkina Faso,"},{"time":170280,"text":"Togo, Nigeria."},{"time":173080,"text":"The Sahel region is that semiarid area\nsouth of the Sahara desert"},{"time":178960,"text":"that extends from the Atlantic\nin the west to the Red Sea in the east."},{"time":185560,"text":"I became more interested in this grain"},{"time":189280,"text":"that was deemed worth taking\nto the afterlife by early Egyptians."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195120,"text":"As I continued my research,"},{"time":197280,"text":"I found out that fonio was actually --"},{"time":202160,"text":"wherever it was cultivated --"},{"time":204160,"text":"there was always some myth,\nor some superstition connected to it."},{"time":208760,"text":"The Dogon,"},{"time":210240,"text":"another great culture in Mali,"},{"time":212120,"text":"called it \"po,\""},{"time":213800,"text":"or, \"the seed of the universe.\""},{"time":216480,"text":"In that ancient culture's mythology,"},{"time":218840,"text":"the entire universe\nsprouted from a seed of fonio."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224440,"text":"Aside from its purported\nmystical properties,"},{"time":227480,"text":"fonio is a miracle grain in many aspects."},{"time":231520,"text":"It is nutritious,"},{"time":233080,"text":"particularly rich\nin methionine and cysteine,"},{"time":236880,"text":"two amino acids that are deficient\nin most other major grains:"},{"time":241280,"text":"barley, rice or wheat to name a few."},{"time":245520,"text":"In addition,"},{"time":246840,"text":"fonio cultivation\nis great for the environment."},{"time":250760,"text":"It tolerates poor soil"},{"time":252800,"text":"and needs very little water,"},{"time":254560,"text":"surviving where nothing else will grow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259680,"text":"As a chef,"},{"time":261160,"text":"what first struck me was\nits delicate taste and its versatility."},{"time":267960,"text":"Similar to couscous,"},{"time":271000,"text":"fonio has a delicious,\nnutty and earthy flavor."},{"time":276080,"text":"It can be turned into salad,"},{"time":278400,"text":"served as noodles,"},{"time":280520,"text":"used in baking"},{"time":282160,"text":"or simply as a substitute for any\nother grains in your favorite recipes."},{"time":287880,"text":"I am happy to share some of my\nfonio sushi and sweet potato sushi"},{"time":294280,"text":"with some of you right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296400,"text":"(Audience) Oh!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":298320,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":300840,"text":"And okra."}]},{"cues":[{"time":307480,"text":"(Audience murmurs)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":311600,"text":"In Kédougou"},{"time":313320,"text":"it is also nicknamed \"ñamu buur,\""},{"time":316640,"text":"which means \"food for royalty,\""},{"time":319160,"text":"and it's served for guests of honor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322160,"text":"Located at the border\nwith Guinea and Mali,"},{"time":326640,"text":"Kédougou first strikes visitors\nwith its stunning vistas"},{"time":330080,"text":"and views of the Fouta Djallon Mountains."},{"time":333200,"text":"Sadly, it is also one of the poorest\nregions of Senegal."},{"time":340320,"text":"Because of desertification\nand lack of job prospects,"},{"time":344160,"text":"much of Kédougou's\nyoung population has left."},{"time":348240,"text":"They chose the deadly path of migration"},{"time":351200,"text":"in search of \"better\" opportunities."},{"time":354920,"text":"Often,"},{"time":357040,"text":"they risk their lives\ntrying to reach Europe."},{"time":361080,"text":"Some leave by crossing the Sahara desert."},{"time":364560,"text":"Others end up on inadequate wooden canoes"},{"time":367960,"text":"in desperate attempts to reach Spain."},{"time":372280,"text":"According to a recent \"Guardian\" article,"},{"time":374920,"text":"by 2020 more that 60 million people\nfrom sub-Saharan Africa"},{"time":380760,"text":"are expected to migrate"},{"time":383120,"text":"due to desertification."},{"time":385080,"text":"This is the biggest global wave\nof migration since the Second World War,"},{"time":390960,"text":"and it's only set to grow."},{"time":394080,"text":"So far this year,"},{"time":396160,"text":"more that 2,100 migrants\nhave lost their lives"},{"time":400280,"text":"on their way to Europe."},{"time":403080,"text":"This is the reality of Kédougou"},{"time":406080,"text":"and of much of the Sahel today."},{"time":409520,"text":"Scary future,"},{"time":411400,"text":"scarce food"},{"time":413200,"text":"and no opportunities\nto change their situation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418040,"text":"If life in your village\nweren't so precarious,"},{"time":422440,"text":"if there was a way\nto having enough food to get by,"},{"time":425840,"text":"or having a paying job --"},{"time":428800,"text":"if you and your sisters"},{"time":430160,"text":"didn't have to spend\n30 percent of their waking hours"},{"time":435520,"text":"fetching water,"},{"time":438240,"text":"if conditions were just\na little more hospitable ..."},{"time":443800,"text":"could the solution\nbe right here in our soil?"},{"time":448280,"text":"Could bringing fonio\nto the rest of the world"},{"time":451200,"text":"be the answer?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":454520,"text":"Ancient grains are getting more popular,"},{"time":456680,"text":"and sales of gluten-free items\nare growing in the US --"},{"time":461480,"text":"16.4 percent since 2013,"},{"time":464720,"text":"making it a 23.3-billion-dollar industry."},{"time":470960,"text":"How could fonio\npartake in this market share?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":475960,"text":"There are many challenges\nin turning fonio into food."},{"time":479360,"text":"Traditional processing\nis laborious and time-consuming,"},{"time":482840,"text":"especially when compared to other grains."},{"time":488720,"text":"Well, thankfully, technology has evolved."},{"time":493520,"text":"And there are now machines"},{"time":496160,"text":"that can process fonio\nin a more efficient way."},{"time":499800,"text":"And as a matter of fact,"},{"time":502200,"text":"a few years ago,"},{"time":503840,"text":"Sanoussi Diakité,"},{"time":505320,"text":"a Senegalese engineer,"},{"time":506600,"text":"won a Rolex prize"},{"time":508840,"text":"for his invention of the first\nmechanized fonio processor."},{"time":513760,"text":"Today, such machines are making life\nmuch easier for producers"},{"time":518679,"text":"around the whole Sahel region."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522840,"text":"Another challenge\nis the colonial mentality"},{"time":527120,"text":"that what comes from the west is best."},{"time":531360,"text":"This tendency to look down\non our own products"},{"time":534400,"text":"and to see crops like fonio\nas simply \"country peoples' food,\""},{"time":538760,"text":"therefore substandard,"},{"time":540640,"text":"explains why even though we don't\nproduce wheat in Senegal traditionally,"},{"time":545800,"text":"it is far easier to find baguettes\nor croissants in the streets of Dakar"},{"time":550280,"text":"than it is to find any fonio products."},{"time":555000,"text":"This same mindset popularized\nthe overprocessed, leftover rice debris"},{"time":561400,"text":"known as \"broken rice,\""},{"time":565120,"text":"which was imported to Senegal\nfrom Indochina"},{"time":568680,"text":"and introduced by the colonial French."},{"time":573600,"text":"Soon, broken rice became\na key ingredient in our national dish,"},{"time":578360,"text":"thiéboudienne,"},{"time":579640,"text":"replacing our own traditional,\nmore nutritious African rice,"},{"time":585120,"text":"Oryza glaberrima."},{"time":588080,"text":"Ironically, the same African rice\ndespised at home"},{"time":592000,"text":"was hailed abroad."},{"time":593440,"text":"Indeed, during the Atlantic slave trade,"},{"time":597480,"text":"this rice became\na major crop in the Americas ..."},{"time":602560,"text":"particularly in the Carolinas"},{"time":604120,"text":"where it was nicknamed, \"Carolina gold.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":608640,"text":"But let's return to fonio."},{"time":611840,"text":"How can we turn its current status\nof \"country-people food\""},{"time":616360,"text":"into a world-class crop?"},{"time":620560,"text":"Last year,"},{"time":622160,"text":"a business partner and I secured\na commitment from Whole Foods Market,"},{"time":626600,"text":"the US's largest natural food store chain,"},{"time":630000,"text":"to carry fonio."},{"time":632000,"text":"And we got a large\nAmerican ingredient importer"},{"time":636920,"text":"interested enough\nto send a team of executives"},{"time":639960,"text":"to West Africa with us"},{"time":641800,"text":"to explore the supply chain's viability."},{"time":646200,"text":"We found ourselves\nobserving manual operations"},{"time":651360,"text":"in remote locations"},{"time":653720,"text":"with few controls over quality."},{"time":656800,"text":"So we started focusing\non processing issues."},{"time":660960,"text":"We drew up a vision"},{"time":662680,"text":"with a beneficial and commercially\nsustainable supply chain for fonio,"},{"time":667480,"text":"and we connected ourselves\nwith organizations"},{"time":670360,"text":"that can help us achieve it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":673360,"text":"Walking backwards from the market,\nhere is what it looks like."},{"time":677640,"text":"Imagine that fonio\nis consumed all across the globe"},{"time":683920,"text":"as other popular ancient grains."},{"time":689320,"text":"Fonio touted on the levels of cereals,"},{"time":692400,"text":"breads,"},{"time":694040,"text":"nutrition bars,"},{"time":696400,"text":"cookies, pastas,"},{"time":698120,"text":"snacks -- why not?"},{"time":700560,"text":"It's easier to say than quinoa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702600,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":705840,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":712080,"text":"To get there,"},{"time":713600,"text":"fonio needs to be readily available"},{"time":716040,"text":"at a consistent quality\nfor commercial users,"},{"time":718800,"text":"such as food manufacturers\nand restaurant chains."},{"time":722640,"text":"That's the part we're missing."},{"time":725040,"text":"To make fonio available\nat a consistent quality"},{"time":728120,"text":"for commercial use,"},{"time":729880,"text":"you need a commercial-scale fonio mill"},{"time":733320,"text":"that adheres to international\nquality standards."},{"time":737360,"text":"Currently, there is no such mill\nin the whole world,"},{"time":741240,"text":"so in our vision,"},{"time":742920,"text":"there is an African-owned\nand operated fonio mill"},{"time":747480,"text":"that processes efficiently"},{"time":750000,"text":"and in compliance with the requirements\nof multinational food companies."},{"time":756360,"text":"It is very difficult\nfor the fonio producers today"},{"time":761680,"text":"to sell and use fonio"},{"time":764240,"text":"unless they devote\na huge amount of time and energy"},{"time":768120,"text":"in threshing, winnowing and husking it."},{"time":771440,"text":"In our vision,"},{"time":772760,"text":"the mill will take on those tasks,"},{"time":775480,"text":"allowing the producers to focus\non farming rather than processing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":782400,"text":"There is untapped\nagricultural capacity in the Sahel,"},{"time":788000,"text":"and all it takes\nis changing market conditions"},{"time":792080,"text":"to activate that capacity."},{"time":795040,"text":"By relieving fonio producers\nof manual operations,"},{"time":799880,"text":"the mill will free up their time"},{"time":802200,"text":"and remove the production bottleneck\nthat limits their output."},{"time":807280,"text":"And there are other benefits as well"},{"time":809520,"text":"in using Sahel land for agriculture."},{"time":815840,"text":"More benefits,"},{"time":817880,"text":"higher employment,"},{"time":820280,"text":"climate change mitigation\nby reversing desertification"},{"time":825360,"text":"and greater food security."},{"time":827680,"text":"Nice vision, right?"},{"time":830120,"text":"Well, we are working\ntowards getting it done."},{"time":833240,"text":"Last month we introduced fonio\nto shoppers in New York City"},{"time":837520,"text":"and online,"},{"time":838760,"text":"in a package that makes it attractive\nand desirable and accessible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":844440,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":852000,"text":"We are talking with operators\nand investors in West Africa"},{"time":856720,"text":"about building a fonio mill."},{"time":859440,"text":"And most importantly,"},{"time":861080,"text":"we have teamed with an NGO\ncalled SOS SAHEL"},{"time":864280,"text":"to recruit, train and equip\nsmallholders in the Sahel"},{"time":869200,"text":"to increase their fonio production."}]},{"cues":[{"time":872600,"text":"Hunger levels are higher\nin sub-Saharan Africa"},{"time":875760,"text":"than any other place in the world."},{"time":879520,"text":"The Sahel population is set to grow"},{"time":882960,"text":"from 135 million to 340 million people."},{"time":888320,"text":"However, in that drought-\nand famine-prone region,"},{"time":892960,"text":"fonio grows freely."},{"time":896360,"text":"This tiny grain may provide big answers,"},{"time":899960,"text":"reasserting its Dogon name,"},{"time":902440,"text":"\"po,\" the seed of the universe,"},{"time":905240,"text":"and taking us one step closer"},{"time":907440,"text":"to the universal civilization."}]},{"cues":[{"time":910520,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":912120,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}